cs.IT, cs.NI, cs.SY, cs.MM, cs.DC 

Reasoning: 
1. cs.IT (Information Theory) - The paper presents an information-theoretic approach to the design of optimal multihop microwave networks that minimizes end-to-end transmission delay. 
2. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - The paper discusses the design of multihop relay networks for low latency communications. 
3. cs.SY (Systems and Control) - The paper deals with the optimization of relay selection in multihop microwave networks, which can be seen as a control problem. 
4. cs.MM (Multimedia) - The paper mentions high-frequency trading as an application that demands low latency communications, which can involve the transmission of multimedia data. 
5. cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) - The paper discusses the use of multihop relay networks for low latency communications, which can be seen as a distributed computing problem.
